#### A. Yield Curve & Policy Rate
```python
# All yields in percent (e.g. 4.25); results in basis points
slope_10y2y_bps = (yield_10y - yield_2y) * 100   # negative = inverted
slope_10y3m_bps = (yield_10y - yield_3m) * 100   # recession-predictive slope
real_yield_10y_bps = (yield_10y - tips_breakeven_10y) * 100  # policy restrictiveness proxy
policy_rate_distance_bps = (effr - 2.5) * 100    # distance to ~neutral (Fed est. 2.5%)
```

#### B. Inflation Trend
```python
cpi_3m_annualised_pct = ((cpi_latest / cpi_3m_ago) ** 4 - 1) * 100
cpi_reacceleration = cpi_3m_annualised_pct > cpi_yoy_12m_pct  # True = re-accelerating
```

#### C. Fama-French Factor Z-Scores
Z-scores locate current factor returns in historical context. Use 60-month (5-year)
rolling mean and std as baseline.
```python
# For each factor f in [HML, SMB, MOM, RMW, CMA]:
# ff_zscores[f] = (trailing_12m_return[f] - mean_60m[f]) / std_60m[f]
# |Z| > 1.5 = unusually strong signal; use to confirm or challenge tilts in Step 4
```

#### D. Credit Spread Percentiles
```python
# Percentile of current spread vs. 5-year history (0 = tightest ever, 100 = widest)
from scipy.stats import percentileofscore
ig_oas_pctile = percentileofscore(ig_oas_5y_history, ig_oas_current)
hy_oas_pctile = percentileofscore(hy_oas_5y_history, hy_oas_current)
# >80 = elevated stress; <20 = complacency
```

#### E. Commodity & Dollar Momentum (3-month %)
```python
wti_mom_pct    = (wti_latest    / wti_3m_ago    - 1) * 100
gold_mom_pct   = (gold_latest   / gold_3m_ago   - 1) * 100
copper_mom_pct = (copper_latest / copper_3m_ago - 1) * 100
# Dollar: EUR/USD falling = USD strengthening (bearish for risk assets)
usd_mom_pct    = (eurusd_3m_ago / eurusd_latest - 1) * 100  # positive = USD stronger
```

